# TypeScript / Node.js

- Use ESM imports (`import` / `export`), not `require`
- Load env vars with `dotenv` at the entry point of each script
- Prefer explicit types on public functions; let inference handle locals
- Handle errors explicitly — log context, then rethrow or exit with a clear message
- Run scripts with `npx tsx <file.ts>` from the project folder — projects use `tsx`, not `ts-node`

```typescript
// Entry point pattern
import "dotenv/config";

async function main() {
  // ...
}

main().catch((err) => {
  console.error(err);
  process.exit(1);
});
```
